WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.400
One of the key reasons President Trump says he went to war with Iran was over its

2
00:00:04.400 --> 00:00:07.520
nuclear material that could be used to develop a weapon.

3
00:00:07.520 --> 00:00:09.920
Now that the US and Iran have agreed a ceasefire,

4
00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:14.640
what's going to happen to its enriched uranium? Trump says he wants it removed.

5
00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:18.560
However, the wording in the ceasefire deal is pretty vague.

6
00:00:18.560 --> 00:00:23.040
It says the fate of Iran's stoppiles will be resolved in further negotiations

7
00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:25.440
that are meant to last up to 60 days.

8
00:00:25.440 --> 00:00:29.040
The agreement does contain a commitment that Iran shall not procure

9
00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:30.800
or develop a nuclear weapon.

10
00:00:30.800 --> 00:00:32.240
But that isn't new.

11
00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:37.280
Similar language was used in the 2015 deal negotiated by the Obama administration

12
00:00:37.280 --> 00:00:39.600
and abandoned by Trump during his first term.

13
00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:45.040
Iran was thought to have enriched uranium up to 60% purity by 2025.

14
00:00:45.040 --> 00:00:49.680
Fuel for most nuclear power stations requires around 3-5% enrichment.

15
00:00:49.680 --> 00:00:52.480
While for nuclear weapons, it's at least 90%.

16
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.320
Iran has always said that its nuclear program was entirely peaceful.

17
00:00:56.320 --> 00:00:59.600
The US has bombed several of Iran's nuclear facilities

18
00:00:59.600 --> 00:01:02.160
but it's unclear what remains of its stoppiles.

